snippet.title: Behind the News
snippet.description:
For the past 50 years, BTN has been a world leader in children's news & kids news. As part of the Australian Broadcasting Corporation, BTN has introduced the news & current events to upper-primary students in Australia and around the world - but it isn't just for kids. BTN assists people of all ages by breaking down current issues and events in a high-energy, fun way - all while providing background information that isn’t usually given by other news bulletins.
 
We have 1000s of stories on all sorts of topics - if you're looking for help to understand something, you'll probably find it on BTN. http://www.abc.net.au/btn/ 

Follow us on Social Media:
TikTok https://www.tiktok.com/@behindthenewstv
Facebook: https://www.facebook.com/abcbtn

snippet.title: Jordan Ware
snippet.description: Jordan Waré is grammy- award winning producer, violinist, and one half of the indie group, October's Child. The trained violinist has performed worldwide with such acts as Madonna, Quincy Jones, Justin TImberlake and Wyclef Jean. A native New Yorker who moved to Los Angeles in mid-2014, Waré has continued to further develop his production sound, producing for numerous up and coming artists including, Avonlea, Elley Duhé & Brent Faiyaz . Waré touts his greatest accolade as co-producing the ballad that would become the hit record, "Where Are Ü Now," featuring Justin Bieber on Diplo and Skrillex's Jack Ü album, which won a Grammy's in 2016 for Best Dance Recording and Best Dance/Electronic Album.

A todas horas, nuestro equipo de 500 periodistas de más de 30 nacionalidades diferentes reúne noticias con una perspectiva imparcial, más allá de los contenidos de los titulares y las voces de toda Europa y el mundo. snippet.title: Maktoob
snippet.description:
Maktoob is a media initiative based Delhi, in India. It was founded in the southern state Kerala, in March, 2014, with an aim of ensuring an equal and unbiased space for discussion, dialogue and dissemination of information and news. Maktoob publishes news and features in English.

In the recent decades, media ownership had concentrated in the hands of few corporations and conglomerates. This has lead to a narrowing of range of voices and opinions being expressed. And here, Maktoob is trying to make a change. Through news, views and analyses of  ground reports, Maktoob aims to play the part of a small media that aids in a big revolution of justice, liberty and equality.

Maktoob showcases continuous efforts to empower individual citizen and promote democratic ideals through the spread of accurate and humanized editorial content.  The Caste, Class conflicts of diverse Indian society is given utmost editorial importance and we stand against the fascist ideologies.

snippet.title: Observer Research Foundation
snippet.description:
ORF’s aim is to encourage voices from all quarters, geographies and gender, both those that fall in and those that question dominant narratives.

ORF seeks to lead and aid policy thinking towards building a strong and prosperous India in a fair and equitable world. It sees India as a country poised to play a leading role in the knowledge age — a role in which it shall be increasingly called upon to proactively ideate in order to shape global conversations, even as it sets course along its own trajectory of long-term sustainable growth.

ORF helps discover and inform India’s choices. It carries Indian voices and ideas to forums shaping global debates. It provides non-partisan, independent, well-researched analyses and inputs to diverse decision-makers in governments, business communities, and academia and to civil society around the world.

Our mandate is to conduct in-depth research, provide inclusive platforms and invest in tomorrow’s thought leaders today.

snippet.title: Open Forum
snippet.description:
글을 읽을 수 있었던 사람들이 그렇지 못했던 사람들을 지배하던 시대가 있었습니다.
지금도 마찬가지입니다. 올바른 지식과 정보를 갖고 있다는 것은 지식정보시대의 핵심입니다.
오픈 포럼은 경험과 신뢰에 바탕을 둔 여러 분야 전문가들의 지식과 지혜를 나누고자 합니다.

We would like to establish a healthy discussion culture within the Korean Community in order to provide reliable information about Korean community issues.
We want to play a role of unbiased media and to form right public opinion.
We will create new contents through YouTube channel to reach out to many Koreans who communicate through SNS.
In the long run, we plan to implement a program targeting 1.5  generation and 2nd generation Korean Americans such that they will be able to integrate organically into the Korean communities.

snippet.title: Joan Planas
snippet.description:
Soy Joan Planas cineasta, fotógrafo y a veces escribo libros. Amo contarte historias para que disfrutes y aprendas con ellas. He expuesto en museos como el Royal Ontario Museum de Canadá y en The Field Museum de Chicago con el documental “Whang Od: La tatuadora Kalinga”, con más de 10 millones de visualizaciones. He dirigido la película "Camino sin límites", documentales, cortometrajes y proyectos multimedia galardonados como BuscandoHistorias.com e impulsé el movimiento Abrazos Gratis. La base de mi trabajo consiste en documentar el ser humano para entendernos y hacer un mundo mejor.

En este canal te voy a recomendar cosas para reflexionar y divertirte con mis videos de crítica de cine, crítica social, humor, entrevistas, y documentales, pero si no te gusta pensar ni que critique a todo el mundo, te vas a enfadar conmigo 😅

Más info en joanplanas.com

snippet.title: indusdotnews
snippet.description:
Aap Media Network believes in an informed and engaged citizenry, essential for a constitutional democracy. We provide relevant, important, timely and accurate news to the audience and opportunities for public discourse and interaction. In doing so, we are accountable to our viewers. We cherish our independence and strive to be objective and fair.

Our news-gathering and analyses seek to meet high editorial standards. We aim to inculcate civility in the discourse, an unfortunate casualty of the race for television rating points.

Our English-language channel, Indus News, aims to present Pakistan’s perspective on issues of regional and global importance through an inside-out view. We believe the viewer receives the greatest benefit from news and analyses in a global-to-local context. In this, we seek to bring to international audiences the complexity often missed in the coverage of this region

snippet.title: The StudyTube Project
snippet.description:
Hello! 

The outbreak of the Coronavirus pandemic is having unprecedented impacts across the world: schools and universities are closing, GCSE and A-Level exams are cancelled - but that doesn’t mean education needs to stop.

So, we’ve decided to do something about it: welcome to The StudyTube Project!

We’ve all teamed up to try and bring calm in these times of high anxiety and stress. Each day for the foreseeable future, we’ll be taking it in turns to teach you something, or share an area of education we’re passionate about or specialize in. This is a channel to keep you busy, keep you learning or even just to give you somewhere to escape to! Any profits made from Adsense will go straight to charities helping fight COVID-19.

Let's come together as a community and support one another through this confusing time.

There will be a brand new video every day at 6pm, as well as regular content on our Instagram: @thestudytubeproject !

snippet.title: Gabriel Jose Rodriguez
snippet.description:
Musician, producer, DJ, and Funk music enthusiast alike, Gabriel hails out of Philadelphia, Pennsylvania. Gabriel drew much of his musical influence from his father, a well-known Latin composer and lead musician for his band La Unica.

Interested in music all his life, Gabriel pursued it further at Eastern University where he completed a degree in Music Composition and Electronic Music.

When he’s not performing, he spends time in his studio creating his own music and completing client projects. Although he is well versed in all genres of music, some of Gabriel’s favorite genres to mix include Funk/Motown, Oldies, Hip Hop, R&B, Top 40, and Pop music.

Aided by a decade of piano lessons and a musically influenced upbringing, Gabriel’s diverse background lends to his effortless ability to blend a variety of genres; creating the perfect backdrop for any event!

snippet.title: MADHU KURUVA
snippet.description:
“The realm of art in unrestricted, undefined and infinite… I just thrive to be a productive contributor in this endless world of artistry.”– MadhuKuruva
Vision: “To dedicate my life to the creation of world class paintings that depict the religious ethos and tradition of India and establish them respectfully on an international platform.”
My Belief… Every soul is artistic and expresses itself in one or the other form. I discovered colors as the mode of expression of my feelings and use them to paint my inner voice on a canvas. I strongly believe that the artistic creation of an artist reflects the way he observes the world and the way he perceives it in his mind.As an avid painter, I love to explore themes and subjects in specific ways to bring life to my characters. For me a painting is worth a thousand words and a form of meditation that I do while creating every single piece of art.

snippet.title: Yves Dhar - Cello Makes Everything Better
snippet.description: Chh-helloooo everyone, and welcome to my Youtube channel!  As a concert cellist, teacher, and innovator, I invite you to join in watching some mostly fun, sometimes probing, and hopefully illuminating videos that revolve around the best instrument in the world.  There should be a little something for everyone -- fun videos for those who are curious about the cello, behind-the-scenes interviews and footage for the serious fans, and advanced instructional "tips" for the obsessed.  Whether you watch just one video or become a loyal subscriber, I hope to show you that the magic of music is all around us, even when we least expect it, and that "Life without cello is cruel!"  Thanks for watching!

snippet.title: PEYTON
snippet.description: Christopher Peyton (artiste name: Peyton) is an American/British singer, songwriter and performer whose career started with the release of his self-penned single A Higher Place on Hed Kandi Records, which topped dance charts worldwide in 2003. Peyton’s voice and lyrics have become synonymous with soulful house, while his trademark gospel-infused uplifting sound borrows inspiration from his childhood as the son of a preacher man in Virginia. Peyton has performed in over sixty countries and across six continents, and has collaborated with many of house music’s beloved all-star producers & DJ's, including the late godfather of house, Frankie Knuckles.  In 2022 Peyton co-founded and launched Revival House Project, a new label and music collective committed to creating high quality dance productions as well as more opportunities for artists.  He currently lives between London, England and Düsseldorf, Germany.  For more info:  https://linktr.ee/PEYTONMUSIC

Welcome to Dreamsea Surf's official YouTube-Channel! This is the place where you'll get exclusive insights into our Surf destinations and the life of our Dreamsea family.

Dreamsea Surf is a place for friends, couples, solo travelers, and everyone who’s looking for active and social holidays. We believe in the human being, the slow travel concept, and that we can inspire others with kindness, friendliness, and happiness. All Dreamsea Surf Camps are carefully designed to create a cozy homey atmosphere to enlighten your senses and to make you feel part of the Dreamsea family. Dreamsea's core is the creation of a broad multicultural community where people can share their culture, values, and fun. Our goal is to create a sustainable, touristic environment by promoting respect for nature, a balanced lifestyle, and active healthy tourism through surf culture while providing unique experiences to people from all over the world.

snippet.title: Victoria Price
snippet.description:
My name is Victoria Price and I love sharing my legacy of Love with the world. 
Some of you know me through the stories I share about my father Vincent Price.
Some of you know me through my writing, my inspirational talks or my daily practice of joy blog.
However you know me is way less important than the message of Love I try to share and live.
I have been living Love as a nomad on the way of being lost -- finding my way back to my heart so I can can share the joy and Love that can transform and heal us and our beautiful planet.
These videos are a small contribution to the global conversation about the Power of Love. 
May we all do whatever we can to take #LoveViral.

snippet.title: TAYYLOR MADE
snippet.description: TAYYLOR MADE, is an American Rapper/Singer, Music Producer/Engineer and DJ hailing from Washington, D.C. Now based in London, she has established herself as an in-demand artist attracting major bookings such as Boiler Room, Lovebox Festival, Converse and Ministry of Sound. TAYYLOR MADE continues to play internationally, extending her reach across cities from New York to Berlin. The Co-Founder and resident DJ at popular East London club night, VIBRATE, TAYYLOR MADE specialises in Hip Hop and emerging club sounds including Trap, Jersey Club, and Future Beats. In the studio, she has worked with major popular artists including Kano, Fred Again, Yxng Bane, RAYE, Kamille and MNEK among others. As she reveals her new projects as a Recording Artist and Music Producer, and given the enthusiastic reception of her debut release supported by Spotify & Dummy Mag - "WET” (165k+ streams) and brand new single "FLEXXX", very exciting things are expected from her in the near future.

snippet.title: Comrade Rhys
snippet.description:
Hello comrades, it's Comrade Rhys. I'm a Welsh Marxist-Leninist who uploads political videos to promote and defend Socialism, as it's my job to inform you, whether you like it or not. I upload a video on this whenever I have the time, as my work schedule and personal life often eats into the time that I have to make videos. The party that I support is the CPB (Communist Party of Britain). I came round to supporting them after undergoing some serious self-criticism over my support for the CPGB-ML who over the years have shown their very reactionary positions. 

I am constantly asked the question of what got me so into Socialism. I cannot answer it with anything better than experiencing life under Capitalism; wage labour, purchasing goods, times of economic crisis etc. I then wanted to start reflecting on that experience through looking at Marxist literature, which is what gave me the informed decision to become a Marxist-Leninist. 

Keep the red flag flying, comrades!

snippet.title: The Harvard Undergraduate LowKeys
snippet.description:
The Harvard LowKeys are an award-winning, gender-neutral a cappella group at Harvard College. Every song performed by the group is arranged by a current member, resulting in an eclectic repertoire consisting of pop, R&B, hip-hop, and everything in between. Each winter or spring, the group embarks on an international tour to spread its love for a cappella – previous destinations include Puerto Rico, Montreal, Paris, New Orleans and San Francisco. The LowKeys are also Harvard's only a cappella group affiliated with Harvard's Public Service Network, regularly putting on charity performances to support causes in the Greater Boston area and beyond.

Learn more about us at www.theharvardlowkeys.com and check us out on FaceBook, Instagram, and Twitter (@harvardlowkeys).

snippet.title: Nathan Zed
snippet.description:
I'm Nathan Zed

"DON'T FORGET TO SUBSCRIBE!!" I type, as I sit at my laptop, the rest of my body completely motionless.The click-clack sound of the keyboard echoing in my ears long after I had finished typing. I remain still for what seems like an eternity, only moving to wipe the single tear streaming from my right eye. "Not like this...", I let the whisper escape my lips loud enough for anyone nearby to hear me.
No one is nearby.

snippet.title: Merlin Fulcher
snippet.description: Merlin Fulcher is an architectural journalist, writer and broadcaster based in London and reporting on key issues affecting economies, society and the built environment in the UK and beyond. Fulcher has more than a decade's experience in architectural reporting and is currently competitions editor, focussing on procurement, for both Architects' Journal and Architectural Review. Since 2017 he has also been director of tours at London's Architecture Foundation based at the Royal College of Art, leading a team of expert guides in the creation of a highly popular programme exploring complex geographic and design themes across the city.  His other writing -- including reviews, analysis and poems -- has been published by Construction News, New Civil Engineer, the Evening Standard, Different Skies, Counterfire and Tribune. Fulcher holds an MA in Modern History from Lady Margaret Hall, University of Oxford. Since 2020, Fulcher has been Vlogging under the banner Untitled UK on YouTube.

snippet.title: Sincerely Danielle
snippet.description: Welcome to Sincerely Danielle, where I share my life, my love, and my struggles with the world. I'm learning to navigate the ups and downs of parenthood, relationships, & self-care. But this channel is more than just a vlog - it's a space where I can be vulnerable, authentic, and real. But don't worry, it's not all serious all the time! My two favorite artists, Whitney Houston & Michael Jackson. Yes, you read that right - I "ship" them as a couple! It may be unconventional, but hey, who says you can't dream, right? And yes, I'm a total "Shipper" - I believe that Whitney & Michael were meant to be together, & I'll be sharing my fictional stories. But this is also a space where I can talk openly about my mental health struggles. As someone who has been diagnosed with major depression and anxiety, I know how tough it can be to speak up about your struggles. But I believe that by sharing my story, I can help others feel less alone & more empowered to seek help.

My love of culture has taken me around the world where I’ve been exposed to some of the most amazing talent. I want to share that talent and culture with the rest of the world because I think it’s super important. This channel is all about bridging cultural gaps.

I'm on a journey to provide a whole lot of value through my experiences and enjoy the process while doing so. There are a multitude amount of goals that I want to fulfill and Youtube is an amazing outlet to really immerse in that journey to fulfillment. Everyone should have the opportunity to find something that makes them wholeheartedly happy and that they look forward doing. 

For me, it is knowing that I did something that made my life better or made someone else's life better each day. I encourage you to find out what makes you happy and what  you cannot get tired of doing. Then, invest everything into making it into a reality. We only live once. Will you live it in regrets or will you get after it?

I live by "Getting better everyday"! Let's get better together each day in every way that we can!

snippet.title: Tait Martinez
snippet.description:
Tait Martinez 's Bio

Tait Martinez.... is a singer/rapper /producer from Birmingham. He makes his own music, co-produce beats, write his own songs and for other artists, and also plays musical instruments such as piano, guitar and saxophone. Tait Martinez is into all kinds of music but mainly jazz, soul music, classical, rnb , electro house, pop and hip-hop. His music style and sound is different from the usual urban artists. Tait Martinez dwells on creating own sound, own style and he is very versatile with a music style which is a merge involving urban / rnb/ jazz, pop music, dance and electro house put together. 
Tait Martinez's interest in music started at a very early young age singing in school choir, church choir, at weddings and other ceremonies/events. Lately he's been recording his material and now has over 20 tracks for his debut album due soon.. The Album is entitled Life Is A Journey. You can follow Lyfe Martinez on twitter - @LyfeMartinez

snippet.title: VOA Thai
snippet.description:
วีโอเอเป็นองค์กรข่าวระหว่างประเทศที่ใหญ่ที่สุดของสหรัฐฯ เผยแพร่ข่าวสารบนสื่อหลายช่องทางเป็นภาษาอังกฤษและภาษาต่างประเทศกว่า 45 ภาษา ผู้รับข่าวสารของเราอยู่ในประเทศที่เข้าถึงสื่อเสรีได้อย่างจำกัดหรือไม่สามารถเข้าถึงสื่อเสรีได้เลย
วีโอเอก่อตั้งขึ้นในปี พ.ศ. 2485 มุ่งมั่นเสนอข่าวที่เป็นความจริง ครอบคลุม และเป็นอิสระ งบประมาณทั้งหมดของวีโอเอมาจากผู้เสียภาษีชาวอเมริกัน เราเป็นส่วนหนึ่งของหน่วยงาน U.S. Agency for Global Media

พันธกิจของวีโอเอและความเป็นอิสระในการทำข่าว กฎบัตรของวีโอเอ รับรองเป็นกฎหมายระบุว่า
1. วีโอเอจะต้องทำงานในฐานะแหล่งข่าวที่น่าเชื่อถือและเป็นที่พึ่งได้อย่างสม่ำเสมอ มีความถูกต้อง เป็นกลางและครบถ้วน
2. วีโอเอจะทำงานเพื่อสะท้อนภาพของประเทศอเมริกา โดยไม่เลือกเสนอเฉพาะส่วนใดส่วนหนึ่งของสังคมสหรัฐฯเท่านั้น ดังนั้นวีโอเอจะเสนอข้อมูลที่สมดุลและมีความครอบคลุมสำหรับความคิดแบบอเมริกันและสถาบันต่างๆของประเทศ
3. วีโอเอจะเสนอรายงานเกี่ยวกับนโยบายของสหรัฐฯอย่างกระจ่างชัดและมีประสิทธิภาพ และจะเสนอประเด็นที่ถูกหยิบยกมาพูดถึงและแสดงความคิดเห็นเกี่ยวกับนโยบายเหล่านั้นอย่างมีความรับผิดชอบ
